Running the website locally:

 1) cd inkscape/
 2) ./manage.py syncdb
 3) ./manage.py migrate
 4) ./manage.py runserver

Deploying the website:

 Using apache and mysql or postgresql.

 1) Deploy to /var/www/www.inkscape.org/
 2) cd /var/www/www.inkscape.org/inkscape
 3) Copy settings_local.py.template to settings_local.py
 4) Edit this new file in your text editor.
 5) Update all values for the live system including
  a) Database server, name and password etc
  b) Email sevice details for smtp, security, password etc
  c) Random secrate key for django's internal use
  d) Keys for any and all services such as twitter, facebook etc
 6) Deploy apache2 configuration correctly (see django docs for details)
 7) ./manage syncdb
 8) ./manage migrate
 9) service apache2 restart or /etc/init.d/apache2 restart

